<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> give heart to someone • give one’s heart to someone</xh5><p> <i>give heart to someone—</i>inspire smb. with confidence; encourage a person: Tom says he hopes his success will <u>give heart to</u> those who have lost their jobs. <i>Cf.: take heart from someone</i>—be encouraged or inspired by a person: During the time I spent in Nigeria I <u>took heart from</u> brand-new converts to the Church.</p><p> <i>give one’s heart to someone</i>—(also: lose one’s heart to someone) fall in love with a person: She grew to womanhood, and <u>gave her heart to</u> one who could not know its worth.</p> </entry>
